# This .dockerignore is the build-context exclusion list for
# Containerfile.bpfman.openshift, which is consumed by Konflux
# (via Cachi2 + buildah). Buildah does not honor the per-file
# <containerfile>.dockerignore convention that buildkit supports,
# so the rules for the openshift build live at the context root.
#
# The other dockerfiles in the tree (Dockerfile.bpfman,
# Dockerfile.bpfman.dev, Dockerfile.csi-sanity) are buildkit-
# driven and ship their own <dockerfile>.dockerignore files,
# which take precedence over this one for their respective
# builds. This file therefore only affects the openshift
# Containerfile build.
#
# When Containerfile.bpfman.openshift goes away, this file
# can go with it.

# In-container build: needs the full source tree but must not
# pull in host-built artefacts. A stale host bin/bpfman,
# dispatcher/*.bpf.o, or .bpf-build-stamp copied into the context
# would overlap with the in-container build outputs and could
# mask "didn't rebuild" bugs.
bin/
dispatcher/*.bpf.o
.bpf-build-stamp

# Heavy/irrelevant trees that never need to be in the build context.
# Note: .git/ exclusion is load-bearing -- with .git/ present,
# `go build` tries to embed VCS info via debug.BuildInfo, and
# Cachi2's source-staging produces a .git/ state that fails the
# git invocation (exit 128).
.git/
.gitignore
*.md
build/
scripts/
